TFA 2017 Call for Papers

The 2017 International Conference of Taiwan Finance Association 
May 19-20, 2017, Hualien, Taiwan
http://www.finance.org.tw
The Taiwan Finance Association (TFA) is pleased to announce that the 2017 annual meeting will be held on May 19-20 2017 in Hualien, Taiwan. The annual meeting will be hosted jointly by the Taiwan Finance Association and the Department of Finance, National Dong Hwa University. The TFA annual meeting has been a leading academic event in Taiwan that provides finance researchers a communicating platform to present and discuss their ideas. It has also been an important forum that brings together academia, government, and practitioner for in-depth discussion of major financial issues. The conference program will include keynote speeches, academic sessions, and panel discussions.
On behalf of the program committee of the 2017 TFA annual meeting, we are now inviting friends and colleagues to submit their papers electronically through http://2017tfa.ndhu.edu.tw. Papers, theoretical, empirical or policy-oriented, are actively solicited but not limited to the following issues: asset pricing, corporate finance, corporate governance, corporate social responsibility, financial accounting, financial derivatives, financial econometrics, financial ethics, financial institutions and financial markets, insurance and risk management, investment and security analysis, real estate finance, sustainable finance, and other finance topics.Journal of Financial Studies will publish special issues for the conference.
【Important Dates】
Conference Dates: 19-20 May 2017
Start of Submission: 1 February 2017
Submission Deadline: 5 March 2017
Notification of Acceptance: 1 April 2017
Registration Deadline: 20 April 2017
【Venue】
College of Management, National Dong Hwa University, No. 1, Sec. 2, Da Hsueh Rd. Shoufeng, Hualien 97401, Taiwan.
